name: Kenn Borek Air DHC-6-300 Twin Otter [C-GKBH] QUICK Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Kenn Borek Air is one of the more unique airlines in North America. With their 20-strong fleet of Twin Otters, they fly into some of the most inhospitable areas on our planet, including a rescue mission to Antarctica in the dead of winter. Pretty sure this particular bird has been there at least once. Anyway, here's C-GKBH taxiing by on Bravo and taking off runway 17L from Zulu, while holding the brakes and making an extremely quick departure. ATC is included, enjoy! 

Thanks for watching!
